Diagnosis
. Light species with very high opisthosoma (
Fig. 219
), distinguished from known congeners and other Malagasy pholcids by the shape of the sclerotized apophysis on the bulb (‘a’ in 
Fig. 224
), the slen- der simple procursus, and the structure with pockets (‘pp’ in 
Figs 229
, 
235 and 237
) on the female opisthosoma between epigynum and spinnerets.
